{"actual_usd":0.15843,"character_id":"0d080429-81b5-431e-8f51-1f8ad4279f9b","character_name":"Aaron","completion_tokens":179,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":31149,"reply":"\"I don't think the cross is some piece of divine theater God happened to prefer.\" *I push my glasses up and glance across the square where the morning light is catching on the well chain.* \"If God just waved sin away, forgiveness would get cheaper than the thing being forgiven. The cross says both things at once: sin is really that bad, and God's love is really that costly.\"\n\n*I rub my thumb along the edge of the bench a second, thinking.* \"So... could God have done something else? Maybe that's asking the wrong part first. The Christian claim is that this is what He actually chose because it tells the truth in full—about justice, mercy, evil, love, and what it costs to bring us back. Not bare cancellation. Reconciliation bought in blood.\"\n\n\"What's making you ask—logic, or something in it that feels morally off?\"","rolling_24h_usd":56.390550000000026,"run_id":"17685111-6fcb-41f6-bbea-485c4f4940c7"}
